---
description: Deployment, CI/CD, and infrastructure standards
globs: Dockerfile*, .github/**/*.yml, docker-compose*, vite.config.*
alwaysApply: true
---

# Docker
- Multi-stage builds: builder → production (smaller final image)
- Use Alpine or Distroless base images
- .dockerignore to exclude node_modules, .git, env files
- Health check endpoint on all services

# CI/CD Pipeline
- Install → Lint → Type Check → Test → Build → Deploy
- Run tests in parallel where possible
- Cache node_modules between runs
- Deploy only if ALL checks pass

# Environment Strategy
- dev: local with hot reload
- staging: production-like, used for QA
- prod: optimized, monitored, auto-scaled

# Environment Variables
- Validate required env vars at startup (fail fast if missing)
- Separate config per environment
- NO defaults for secrets in code

# Monitoring
- Health check endpoint: /health (200 = healthy)
- Structured logging with correlation IDs
- Error tracking integration (Sentry)
- Basic metrics: request count, latency, error rate
